Chips.title: Wood Chip
Chips.description: Nanocellulose (a wood-derived material) is a viable alternative for semiconducting material (e.g. silicon) that make up the support layer (“substrate”) for today’s computer chips.

Batteries.title: Algae Battery
Batteries.description: Algae has the potential to be used as bio-batteries. It works similarly to typical solar cells; it captures sunlight, stores it, and converts it to electric current.
